  "title": "Trainee Teacher (Place-and-Train Programme)",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Programme:</strong></p><p>Join our Place-and-Train (P&T) programme and kickstart your career in early childhood education. This structured programme combines on-the-job training with sponsored professional qualifications, preparing you to become a fully qualified childcare teacher while gaining hands-on experience in a preschool environment.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Support teachers in daily classroom activities and routines.</p></li><li><p>Assist in caring for children, including supervising play, routines, and basic hygiene.</p></li><li><p>Observe and learn from experienced teachers to develop foundational teaching and classroom management skills.</p></li><li><p>Participate in training workshops, assessments, and sponsored diploma/qualification courses.</p></li><li><p>Assist in maintaining classroom tidiness, cleaning toys and Montessori teaching materials.</p></li><li><p>Contribute to school events, activities, and other initiatives.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or degree in any discipline (fresh graduates, career switchers, and those without preschool experience are welcome).</p></li><li><p>Passion for working with young children and strong communication skills.</p></li><li><p>Willingness to learn and commit to the Place-and-Train programme.</p></li><li><p>Positive attitude, teamwork spirit, and eagerness to grow in the early childhood sector.</p></li></ul><p><strong>What We Offer:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Sponsored early childhood teaching diploma/qualification while you work.</p></li><li><p>Hands-on mentoring and professional development support.</p></li><li><p>Competitive salary during the training period.</p></li><li><p>Clear progression to a fully qualified childcare teacher role upon successful completion.</p></li></ul><p><strong>How to Apply:</strong><br />Submit your resume via MyCareersFuture </p>",
